Kiss My Ride is back and Kenyans have been waiting. Over 100,000 participants registered on the Kiss My Ride website for a chance to win a Brand New Car. But how much do you know about this awesome car up for grabs? Here are some things to know about this car 1. Performance on par: This car is quick for its size and does 0-100 km/h in the sub-12-second range with a top speed of 180 km/h 2. Great interior: The build quality is top rate with smooth plastics and light to touch door panels. 3. A good size boot: The boot size is competitive and is 268 litres . 4. Economy: The car is light weight with a well-sorted small-capacity 1,2-litre non-turbo engine equals great fuel economy. Fuel consumption is rated by the manufacturer at 4,9 litres/100 km Winner This Friday, one winner will walk away with the brand new car. All that was required was a simple registration on the Kiss 100 website (https://kiss100.co.ke/kissmyride/ ) leaving correct details and then making sure you're tuned in to Kiss 100 every day to listen if your name will be called out on air. Everyday 9am, 2pm and 5pm, there was a draw. If you had successfully registered and your name called out on air, you had exactly 15 minutes to call and claim your entry. That entry will be a key which gave you a chance to win the car. On Friday 21 May, 34 entrants will be invited to try whether their key opens the car. Whoever's key opens the car will be the lucky winner who walks away with a brand new car.